<emphasis box="[454,706,1761,1784]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Eotrechus pilicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[718,771,1760,1784]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[718,771,1760,1784]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(male): (1) right fore leg; (2) abdominal venter (genitalia excluded); (3) mid trochanter and part of femur; (4) hind trochanter and part of femur; (5) proctiger (dorsal); (6) pygophore, dorsal view; (7) same, ventral view; (8) same, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,284,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
So far, this is the fifth 
